# 08_toolbar_walk — the radio invariant, proven by script.
#
# Walks a sequence of tool buttons, clicking each one and asserting:
#   1. The clicked button reads as active.
#   2. The previously-active button reads as inactive.
#
# That's the radio invariant: among the toolbar's tool toggles, one
# and only one is active at any time. Pre-s188 this was a property
# we trusted by visual inspection — there was no way to script it.
# Post-s188 m1, with all 15 tool buttons addressable by abbrev, we
# can walk the toolbar and prove the invariant verb-by-verb.
#
# The walk visits a representative sample (not exhaustive) to keep
# the script readable. Add lines for any tool you want to exercise.
#
# Test protocol:
#   1. Open the Scripter window.
#   2. Load this script.
#   3. Run. Watch the toolbar visually flip through tools.
#   4. Every line should PASS.
#
# This is also a nice demo with the pacing knob (s187 m4): crank it
# to 200-300ms and the script becomes a watchable animation of the
# toolbar driving itself.

# ── Start from a known state ────────────────────────────────────────
# Click Select. Whatever was active before, Select is now active.
tb_sel click
assert tb_sel active == true

# ── Walk through the Creation section ───────────────────────────────
# Each click activates the new tool. The radio invariant says the
# previously-active tool deactivates automatically — we assert both
# sides at each step.
tb_nod click
assert tb_nod active == true
assert tb_sel active == false

tb_pen click
assert tb_pen active == true
assert tb_nod active == false

tb_rec click
assert tb_rec active == true
assert tb_pen active == false

tb_ova click
assert tb_ova active == true
assert tb_rec active == false

tb_lin click
assert tb_lin active == true
assert tb_ova active == false

# ── Jump into the Utility section ───────────────────────────────────
# Different visual region of the toolbar; same invariant.
tb_zom click
assert tb_zom active == true
assert tb_lin active == false

tb_meas click
assert tb_meas active == true
assert tb_zom active == false

# ── Return to Select ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# End in a known state so subsequent script runs start clean.
tb_sel click
assert tb_sel active == true
assert tb_meas active == false
